2002/04/11
	RELEASE 1.5.1

	Cleaned up mixin classes to be more cooperative; 
	Cleaned up Rednode's use of mixins 

	redfoot.xml.handler.HandlerBase is now subclassed to take care of
	the different needs of RDF and Redcode parsing

	split off neighbour management code

	Refactored Run / RedNode yet again and... Documented them!

	RedNode no longer has a local, but now is the local and contains
	its neighbourhood and neighbours as attributes. 
	

	RELEASE 1.5.0

	Replaced Redfoot's own HTTP server code with Medusa.

	Changed directory structure to make division between core,
	components, doc and examples more pronounced.

	Added setup.py scripts to the various.

	Cleaned up interface for getting a Rednode up and runing, as well
	as command line options.

	Removed auto reloading of python and redcode modules.


See also:
	redfoot-core/CHANGELOG
	redfoot-components/CHANGELOG
	redfoot-doc/CHANGELOG
	redfoot-examples/CHANGELOG